    <h1>Adieu Paris, Ma&#xAD;tu&#xAD;idi joins Becks at Mi&#xAD;ami</h1>
    <h2></h2>
    <section>
        <a href="/singapore/the-straits-times/textview" title="The Straits Times">The Straits Times</a>
        - <a href="/singapore/the-straits-times/20200814/textview" title="The Straits Times - 2020-08-14"><time>2020-08-14</time></a>
        - <span>SPORT</span>
        - <span role="byline"></span>
    </section>

    <p>MI­AMI • France mid­fielder Blaise Ma­tu­idi will join David Beck­ham’s Ma­jor League Soc­cer club In­ter Mi­ami, the Amer­i­can top-flight club an­nounced yesterday.</p>
    <p>The 33-year-old, who won the 2018 World Cup with Les Bleus, left Ital­ian cham­pi­ons Ju­ven­tus by mu­tual con­sent on Wed­nes­day.</p>
    <p>Ma­tu­idi is the big­gest name to join fledg­ling In­ter, whose de­but match was in March, and Beck­ham could not hide his de­light, call­ing his for­mer Paris Saint-Ger­main team­mate an “ex­cit­ing and gifted player and a great per­son”.</p>


